"A JavaScript object is treated as an async generator if it's :js:data:"
"`Symbol.toStringTag` is ``\"AsyncGenerator\"``. Most likely this will be "
"because it is a true async generator produced by the JavaScript runtime, but "
"it may be a custom object trying hard to pretend to be an async generator. "
"It should have :js:meth:`~AsyncGenerator.next`, :js:meth:`~AsyncGenerator."
"return`, and :js:meth:`~AsyncGenerator.throw` methods."
